TY  - JOUR
AU  - Allen, Franklin
AU  - Morris, Stephen
AU  - Shin, Hyun Song
T1  - Beauty Contests and Iterated Expectations in Asset Markets
PY  - 2006
Y1  - 2006/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhj036
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 19
IS  - 3
SP  - 719
EP  - 752
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - In a financial market where traders are risk averse and short lived and prices are noisy, asset prices today depend on the average expectation today of tomorrow’s price. Thus (iterating this relationship) the date 1 price equals the date 1 average expectation of the date 2 average expectation of the date 3 price. This will not, in general, equal the date 1 average expectation of the date 3 price. We show how this failure of the law of iterated expectations for average belief can help understand the role of higher-order beliefs in a fully rational asset pricing model.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhj036
ER  - 



